In England, in the seven days to 23 February, there were 60,693 new confirmed cases (107.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 February, there were 72,452 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (11,759 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 28 February is 3,658,352 (6,499.5 cases per 100,000 population).
